		"viz_title_story": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "## 📋 Executive Intelligence Brief",
				"fontColor": "#ffffff",
				"backgroundColor": "transparent"
			}
		},
		"viz_story": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### What Splunk Found — Across Your Cisco Estate\n\n---\n\n#### 🚨 Correlated Threat: Compromised Endpoint 10.1.50.22\nSplunk correlated signals from **XDR** (3 active incidents), **Secure Network Analytics** (7 behavioral anomalies — data exfiltration pattern), **Firewall** (847 blocked C2 connections), and **ISE** (posture failure — missing AnyConnect patch). **This is a single compromised host being tracked across 4 different Cisco security products in one view.** Traditional tools would require checking each console individually.\n\n#### 📊 Bandwidth Alert: Dallas MPLS at 96%\nThe Dallas branch MPLS circuit is at **96% utilization** — driven by video conferencing traffic. The internet DIA is at 71%. **Recommendation:** Enable SD-WAN policy to offload WebEx/Teams traffic to the direct internet circuit. This also explains degraded Catalyst Center health score (52/100) for Dallas.\n\n#### 👥 Daily User Report: 1,775 Connected Users\n- **HQ**: 1,259 users (412 wired + 847 wireless)\n- **Dallas**: 223 users — highest wireless density per AP\n- **Chicago**: 165 users — cleanest site\n- **Atlanta**: 128 users\n\nFloor 2 APs in HQ are experiencing **94% channel utilization** — co-channel interference is impacting 203 wireless users. RRM tuning recommended.\n\n#### 📧 Email Security: 17 Malware + 89 Phishing Blocked\nOut of 24,891 emails processed today: 3,421 spam blocked (13.7%), 89 phishing attempts caught, 17 malware attachments quarantined, and **6 DLP violations** detected — Social Security Numbers found in outbound email. **Immediate HR/Legal notification recommended.**\n\n#### 🏢 Data Center: BGP Peer Down + Fabric Congestion\nNexus 93180YC-02 has a **BGP neighbor DOWN** (hold timer expired). Nexus 9332D spine is showing fabric congestion at 82% from bursty compute rack traffic. UCS memory at 91% from Nutanix CVM pressure. **Combined, these represent a risk to east-west data center traffic.**\n\n#### ⚙️ Compliance Gap: 23 Non-Compliant + 8 Critical PSIRT\n23 devices are running outdated IOS-XE and 8 devices have a **critical PSIRT advisory (CVE-2024-20359)**. 34 endpoints failed ISE posture — missing latest AnyConnect. **Patch window recommended within 48 hours.**\n\n#### 👁️ ThousandEyes: ISP Issue Detected\n5 active alerts — **AT&T Chicago peering point congestion** causing SAP ERP path latency to spike from 45ms to 187ms with 4.2% packet loss. Microsoft 365 path is unaffected (22ms). **This is an ISP problem, not your network.**\n\n---\n\n*This intelligence brief was generated by correlating data from 14 Cisco product families in a single Splunk deployment. No other platform can do this.*",
				"fontColor": "#cccccc",
				"backgroundColor": "#1a1c23"
			}
		}
